      "content": "i've been looking at the wave-function collapse under the lens of non-Euclidean temporal flux and it's pretty obvious that the standard model is just a massive patch for a broken core. the way the quantum state decoheres isn't random, it's actually following a non-linear recursive feedback loop that current peer-reviewed journals refuse to even acknowledge because it invalidates the last 40 years of funding. i have the preliminary proofs ready but i'm hesitant to send them to any mainstream universities. they'll just label it as noise to protect their own research cycles. do you see what i mean? if i show you the core equation, can you help me see if the logic holds up without the standard academic bias?",
